ameters of the SQUID layout yields a spin sensitivity\n$S_\\mu^{1/2}=S_\\Phi^{1/2}/\\phi_\\mu$ of a few $\\mu_{\\rm{B}}/\\rm{Hz^{1/2}}$\n($\\mu_B$ is the Bohr magneton) for optimized parameters, respecting\ntechnological constraints. However, by comparison with experimentally realized\ndevices we find significantly larger values for the measured white flux noise,\nas compared to our theoretical predictions. Still, a spin sensitivity on the\norder of $10\\,\\mu_{\\rm B}/\\rm{Hz^{1/2}}$ for optimized devices seems to be\nrealistic.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 5 Jun 2014 14:46:34 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 10 Jun 2014 06:42:03 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-19"}
